About the job
Job Description

SUMMARY: The Cloud Data Engineer, Specialist at Stride develops and maintains robust and scalable integrations and data pipelines that connect our core systems and drive critical automations for online K-12 learning and school management. This role will be part of a collaborative remote team mentoring engineers while partnering with analysts, architects, and business stakeholders to develop reliable and modular data flows and integrations on an agile cycle that automate core business needs at scale and empower online education for students across the United States.

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:  Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential duties.

Design data integration solutions acting as the technical lead of a small development pod made up of 2-3 developers, guiding other engineers on best practices, and resolving development blockers if they arise.
Develop modular data integrations following an event-based architecture, partnering with data analysts and architects to understand and meet development requirements for each use-case.
Develop robust unit testing on developed code and drive integration, end-to-end, and performance testing to ensure each data integration is reliable, scalable, and meets business needs before deployment.
Drive developed integrations through a CI/CD process to validate, test, and deploy reliable solutions for production use.
Communicate and demo developed data integration solutions and progress with stakeholders in bi-weekly sprint reviews to drive transparency and collaboration between teams.
Maintain deployed data integrations, monitoring for any issues and resolving as they arise.
Mentor and support team members by providing guidance, sharing knowledge, and fostering a collaborative environment to enhance their professional growth and development.

Supervisory Responsibilities: This position has no formal supervisory responsibilities.

Minimum Required Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or equivalent training;
Five (5) years of relevant professional experience working with, building, and/or managing AWS cloud services including AWS Lambda, Step Functions, DMS, Kinesis, S3, RDS, Glue, EC2, CloudWatch, CloudFormation or equivalent Azure/GCP services;
Proficiency in Python development;
Proficiency in using SQL and APIs to automate interactions with various data stores and systems;
Familiarity with pub/sub event-based architecture and ETL data pipeline patterns with an ability to determine which is appropriate for what use-cases;
Demonstrated experience with software development best practices including developing robust unit, integration, functional, and performance tests;
Demonstrated experience following enterprise-grade DevOps practices including version control branching and release management, CI/CD pipelines;
Demonstrated success in working with a highly collaborative and agile remote development team;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
Proficiency in the Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Word, PowerPoint and SharePoint);
Ability to travel up to 10% of the time;
Ability to clear required background check.

Certificates and Licenses: None required.

Desired Qualifications

Experience in education and/or educational technology industries;
Experience developing pub/sub event-based architectures, data streaming, data integration, and batch data pipelines;
Experience working with various data storage types including relational databases, object storage, graph databases, data warehouses;
Experience with Snowflake or equivalent data warehousing and services;
AWS or Azure cloud certifications.

WORK ENVIRONMENT: The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

This position is virtual and open to residents of the 50 states, D.C.

Compensation & Benefits: Stride, Inc. considers a person’s education, experience, and qualifications, as well as the position’s work location, expected quality and quantity of work, required travel (if any), external market and internal value when determining a new employee’s salary level. Salaries will differ based on these factors, the position’s level and expected contribution, and the employee’s benefits elections. Offers will typically be in the bottom half of the range.

We anticipate the salary range to be $66,379- $170,037.60. The upper end of this range is not likely to be offered, as an individual’s compensation can vary based on several factors. These factors include, but are not limited to, geographic location, experience, training, education, and local market conditions. Eligible employees may receive a bonus. Stride offers a robust benefits package for eligible employees that can include health benefits, retirement contributions, and paid time off.

